Package Concepts

Class DerivedConcept

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractObjects.ItemWithId
      • Concepts.Concept
        • Concepts.SetConcept
          • Concepts.DerivedConcept
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataObject

    public class DerivedConcept
extends SetConcept
    A derived concept is a concept which is a subconcept of some superconcepts, together with a filter on the subconcepts of the derived concept. Example:
    Concept Student with attribute semester
    DerivedConcept Freshmen, subconcept of Student, with filter: semester = 1.

    Example: Concepts Ship and Car with attribute age.
    DerivedConcept: OldAmphibiousVehicle, subconcept of Ship and Car, with filter age ≥ 20.
    The class provides methods for repositioning the concepts in the concept hierarchy if a new DerivedConcept is defined, or the attributes of existing concepts have been changed.
